<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="220" pageId="17" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1413,1978]" pageId="17" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,442,1701,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="216">Diagnostic features.</emphasis>
Face yellow, with scattered long and white hairs; frons yellow; postgena slightly extended posteriorly as a blunt process; lower one-third of occiput yellow, remainder black with long white hairs; vertex black (
<number box="[317,344,1773,1798]" pageId="17" pageNumber="216" value="11.0">11</number>
b, f); scape yellow, pedicel blackish brown, first flagellomere black; pronotum yellow with blackish brown mark dorsomedially; mesonotum yellow, with dense long white hairs throughout, with three longitudinal black stripes; lateral stripe extends from level of anterior spiracle to posterior margin of postalar calli, median stripe extends from anterior margin of mesonotum triangularly to three-fourths length of mesonotum with straight posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[446,528,1917,1942]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,249,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Platypygus melinoproctus: a — adult male (lateral view), b — head (anterolateral view), c — female abdomen (dorsal view), d — female mesonotum (dorsal view), e — male abdomen (dorsal view), f — female head (anterior view), g — wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248560/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[500,528,1917,1942]" pageId="17" pageNumber="216" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
d); scutellum yellow with black mark basomedially, with dense long white hairs (
<figureCitation box="[159,240,1953,1978]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,249,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Platypygus melinoproctus: a — adult male (lateral view), b — head (anterolateral view), c — female abdomen (dorsal view), d — female mesonotum (dorsal view), e — male abdomen (dorsal view), f — female head (anterior view), g — wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248560/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,240,1954,1978]" pageId="17" pageNumber="216" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
a); halter yellow; r-m crossvein about the middle of cell dm (
<figureCitation box="[920,1001,1953,1978]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,249,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Platypygus melinoproctus: a — adult male (lateral view), b — head (anterolateral view), c — female abdomen (dorsal view), d — female mesonotum (dorsal view), e — male abdomen (dorsal view), f — female head (anterior view), g — wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/248560/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[973,1001,1954,1978]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="216" unit="g" value="11.0">11</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g).
</paragraph>
