<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,620,645]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Remarks</emphasis>
. Neither Efflatoun (
<number box="[536,594,620,645]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="1945.0">1945</number>
) nor Steyskal &amp; El Bialy (
<number box="[898,956,620,645]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="1967.0">1967</number>
) treated 
<taxonomicName box="[1057,1245,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Platypygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melinoproctus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1245,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">P. melinoproctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their work on the Egyptian bombyliids and El Hawagry (
<number box="[669,727,656,680]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" value="2011.0">2011</number>
) did not include it in his checklist of Egyptian species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,340,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Mythicomyiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mythicomyiidae</taxonomicName>
. We have thus deleted 
<collectingCountry box="[595,662,693,717]" name="Egypt" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Egypt</collectingCountry>
from the current known range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
